  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best schools in Hyderabad for 8th class?",
  "response": "When looking for the best schools for an 8th class student in Hyderabad, several highly regarded institutions stand out. Here are a few of the top schools known for their quality education, facilities, and academic performance:\n\n1. **Hyderabad Public School (HPS)**\n   - **Location:** Begumpet\n   - **Overview:** HPS is one of the oldest and most prestigious schools in Hyderabad. It offers a well-rounded education with a strong emphasis on academics, sports, and extracurricular activities.\n\n2. **Delhi Public School (DPS)**\n   - **Location:** Nacharam\n   - **Overview:** DPS is known for its excellent curriculum, modern facilities, and holistic approach to education. It focuses on both academic excellence and the overall development of students.\n\n3. **Oakridge International School**\n   - **Location:** Gachibowli and Bachupally\n   - **Overview:** Oakridge follows an international curriculum and is known for its global perspective and state-of-the-art facilities. It is an excellent choice for students aiming for international education standards.\n\n4. **Chirec International School**\n   - **Location:** Kondapur and Gachibowli\n   - **Overview:** Chirec is renowned for its innovative teaching methods and focus on individual student growth. The school offers both national and international curricula.\n\n5. **Bharatiya Vidya Bhavan's Public School**\n   - **Location:** Jubilee Hills and Basheerbagh\n   - **Overview:** Known for its strong academic record and value-based education, BVB offers a nurturing environment for students to grow academically and personally.\n\n6. **Nasr School**\n   - **Location:** Gachibowli and Khairtabad\n   - **Overview:** Nasr School is known for its disciplined environment and focus on holistic education. It offers a curriculum that balances academics with extracurricular activities.\n\n7. **Sreenidhi International School**\n   - **Location:** Moinabad\n   - **Overview:** This school is known for its integrated approach to education, combining academics with sports and other extracurricular activities to develop well-rounded students.\n\nWhen choosing a school, it's important to consider factors such as the curriculum offered (CBSE, ICSE, State Board, or International), the school's location, fees, facilities, and the specific needs and interests of your child. It's also helpful to visit the schools and meet with the staff to get a better sense of which environment would be the best fit for your child.",
